WEBVTT

00:02.567 --> 00:05.570
[COOP'S HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05.614 --> 00:08.399
KIM NITTY, RAPPING:
♪ NO QUESTIONS ASKED

00:08.443 --> 00:11.054
♪ I'M AT THE TOP, I JUST MIGHT
BUILD ME A HOUSE ON THE MOON ♪

00:11.098 --> 00:14.231
♪ YOU CAN TELL THAT I'M GREAT,
ONCE I'M DONE, I'M
GETTIN' TO IT ♪

00:14.275 --> 00:17.582
♪ I'LL KEEP IT MOVIN',
NEVER NO STOPPIN' ME,
I'M A BLAST ♪

00:17.626 --> 00:21.064
♪ NO QUESTIONS ASKED,
NO QUESTIONS ASKED ♪

00:21.108 --> 00:23.066
[MUSIC STOPS]
LAYLA: THAT WAS GREAT,

00:23.110 --> 00:25.112
REALLY GREAT.
KIM: THANK YOU. APPRECIATE IT.

00:25.155 --> 00:27.114
I WANT TO TRY
A FEW THINGS,
JUST ADD A COUPLE

00:27.157 --> 00:28.767
DIFFERENT BEATS.
CAN YOU STICK
AROUND FOR A BIT?

00:28.811 --> 00:31.074
YEAH, FOR SURE.

00:31.118 --> 00:33.685
SO, SHE MY REPLACEMENT?

00:33.729 --> 00:36.427
I'M--I'M JUST TRYING
OUT A FEW ARTISTS.

00:36.471 --> 00:38.081
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE
REALLY DOING THIS.

00:38.125 --> 00:39.691
COOP, I TOLD YOU.

00:39.735 --> 00:42.085
THIS IS MY SONG, LAYLA.
I WROTE IT.

00:42.129 --> 00:44.696
IT'S OUR SONG, AND WE
NEVER GOT A CHANCE

00:44.740 --> 00:46.481
TO FINISH IT, JUST LIKE
THE OTHER ONES.

00:46.524 --> 00:48.918
SO YOU JUST WHAT,
GIVE IT TO SOMEONE ELSE?

00:48.961 --> 00:50.789
[SCOFFS]
LIKE FATHER, LIKE
DAUGHTER, I SEE.

00:50.833 --> 00:53.662
- WHAT IS THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?
- EXACTLY WHAT I SAID.

00:53.705 --> 00:56.665
PATIENCE WROTE A SONG,
AND YOUR POPS GAVE IT
TO SOMEONE ELSE.

00:56.708 --> 00:59.276
WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE?
[LAYLA EXHALES SHARPLY]

00:59.320 --> 01:03.280
I'M NOT GONNA SIT HERE
AND LET YOU DISRESPECT
ME IN MY OWN STUDIO.

01:03.324 --> 01:06.109
I INVESTED VIRTUALLY
ALL MY TIME AND MONEY

01:06.153 --> 01:08.807
INTO PRODUCING
THESE TRACKS THAT ARE
STILL INCOMPLETE.

01:08.851 --> 01:11.332
YOU QUIT ON ME,
COOP, WITHOUT EVEN
TELLING ME,

01:11.375 --> 01:13.551
SO WHAT I CHOOSE TO DO
WITH THESE TRACKS

01:13.595 --> 01:16.728
TO MAKE THE BEST OUT OF
A DIFFICULT SITUATION
IS MY BUSINESS.

01:16.772 --> 01:19.949
WHATEVER. GOOD LUCK WITH
YOUR REPLACEMENT COOP.

01:21.864 --> 01:25.172
OLIVIA: FROM MY PODCAST,
I'VE TRIED TO AT LEAST
GIVE A SMALL VOICE

01:25.215 --> 01:29.915
TO SOME INJUSTICES
THAT WOULD HAVE OTHERWISE
GONE COMPLETELY UNNOTICED.

01:32.266 --> 01:34.050
OH, THAT'S IT?

01:34.094 --> 01:35.834
- SHOULD I SAY MORE?
- NO, NO, THAT'S GOOD.

01:35.878 --> 01:38.098
OK, ASK ME
THE NEXT QUESTION.

01:38.141 --> 01:40.709
SPENCER: YOU REALLY NEED TO BE
REHEARSING YOUR ANSWERS?
[OLIVIA SIGHS]

01:40.752 --> 01:43.320
SPENCER: JUST BE YOU.
THEY'RE GONNA LOVE YOU.
[OLIVIA GROANS]

01:43.364 --> 01:46.149
- I KNOW. I JUST--
I REALLY WANT THIS.
- I KNOW.

01:46.193 --> 01:49.413
GRACE: WANT WHAT?
SPENCER: LIV'S GOT A BIG-TIME
JOB INTERVIEW IN AN HOUR.

01:49.457 --> 01:52.460
OLIVIA: IT'S FOR A SUMMER JOB
AT THE "L.A. TRIBUNE" ONLINE.

01:52.503 --> 01:55.811
OK. HEH!
LOOK AT YOU BEING GREAT.

01:55.854 --> 01:59.119
THANK YOU. WELL, I SHOULD
PROBABLY GET GOING.

01:59.162 --> 02:01.164
WISH ME LUCK.

02:02.774 --> 02:05.342
[KISS]
SPENCER: GOOD LUCK.
OLIVIA: THANK YOU.

02:05.386 --> 02:07.823
BYE, MS. GRACE.
GRACE: BYE.

02:07.866 --> 02:09.781
[DOOR CLOSES]
SO HOW YOU FEELING?

02:09.824 --> 02:11.218
I STILL AIN'T
HEARD ANYTHING
FROM COACH DANTE

02:11.261 --> 02:12.958
SINCE HE RESIGNED
FROM TOLEDO.

02:13.002 --> 02:15.439
- MM-HMM.
- I MEAN, THAT MAN
RECRUITED ME,

02:15.483 --> 02:17.441
CONVINCED ME
TO SIGN WITH 'EM.

02:17.485 --> 02:20.096
THE LEAST HE CAN DO
IS CALL ME BACK
WITH AN EXPLANATION.

02:20.140 --> 02:22.185
- WHAT ABOUT THE HEAD COACH?
- COACH HUDSON?

02:22.229 --> 02:24.187
YEAH, HE'S STOPPING BY
THE SCHOOL LATER TODAY.

02:24.231 --> 02:26.189
HE WANTS TO CHECK IN
AND SHOW ME HOW THEY'RE

02:26.233 --> 02:28.278
BUILDING
THE ENTIRE OFFENSE
AROUND ME NEXT YEAR.

02:28.322 --> 02:30.454
- THAT'S EXCITING.
- YEAH, I GUESS.

02:30.498 --> 02:32.674
- SPENCER.
- DO YOU THINK THEY KNEW

02:32.717 --> 02:34.980
COACH DANTE WAS LEAVING
WHEN I SIGNED WITH 'EM?

02:35.024 --> 02:36.982
ACTUALLY, NEVER MIND.

02:37.026 --> 02:39.202
NEVER MIND.
I'M JUST IN MY HEAD.

02:39.246 --> 02:42.292
JUST ASK COACH HUDSON
WHEN HE COME DOWN
TO THE SCHOOL TODAY.

02:42.336 --> 02:45.295
AND REMEMBER, YOU WOULDN'T
BE THE FIRST PLAYER

02:45.339 --> 02:47.428
WHO BACKED OFF
OF A COMMITMENT,

02:47.471 --> 02:49.647
BUT DON'T WRITE
THEM OFF JUST YET.

02:49.691 --> 02:52.607
TOLEDO STATE IS STILL
AN INCREDIBLE OPPORTUNITY.

03:01.703 --> 03:04.271
JORDAN: I GO
TO JUNIOR COLLEGE,
I BALL OUT,

03:04.314 --> 03:07.926
AND TWO YEARS FROM NOW,
I HAVE MULTIPLE OFFERS
FROM D1 SCHOOLS.

03:07.970 --> 03:09.928
SOUNDS LIKE
A GOOD PLAN.

03:09.972 --> 03:11.930
WELL, MY DAD
AND COACH MONTES THINK

03:11.974 --> 03:14.324
IT'S THE BEST OPTION
FOR ME, SO...

03:14.368 --> 03:16.326
DO YOU?

03:16.370 --> 03:18.328
I KNOW IT'S
THE RIGHT MOVE,

03:18.372 --> 03:20.983
BUT HONESTLY, ASH, AFTER
THE SEASON THAT I HAD,

03:21.026 --> 03:23.594
EVEN WITH THE CONCUSSIONS,
IT STINGS TO KNOW

03:23.638 --> 03:26.249
THAT NOT ONE
D1 COACH WANTED ME.

03:26.293 --> 03:29.252
- YOU KNOW WHAT STINGS
EVEN MORE THAN THAT?
- HMM?

03:29.296 --> 03:31.254
NOT BEING ABLE TO PLAY
FOOTBALL EVER AGAIN.

03:31.298 --> 03:34.257
- UH, ASH, I'M--I'M SORRY.
- NO, NO, HEY, LOOK,

03:34.301 --> 03:36.259
I'M NOT GUILT-TRIPPING YOU.
I GET IT.

03:36.303 --> 03:38.566
YOU DESERVE A D1 OFFER.

03:38.609 --> 03:40.524
- THANKS.
- JUST REMEMBER
HOW LUCKY YOU ARE.

03:40.568 --> 03:42.483
YOU GET TO KEEP
PLAYING FOOTBALL,

03:42.526 --> 03:46.138
SO GO BALL OUT, STARTING
WITH THAT ALL-AMERICAN
GAME THIS WEEK.

03:46.182 --> 03:50.142
YEAH, WELL, I'M A RESERVE.
I MEAN, THERE'S NO CHANCE
I EVEN SEE THE FIELD.

03:50.186 --> 03:53.102
HELL, I SHOULD--I SHOULD
BE UP IN THE STANDS
WITH YOU, RIGHT?

03:53.145 --> 03:56.714
UH, I WON'T BE THERE.
I'M JUST NOT READY TO BE
AROUND FOOTBALL YET.

03:56.758 --> 03:59.239
I'LL BE ROOTING FOR YOU
TO GET INTO THE GAME.

03:59.282 --> 04:01.893
- RIGHT, YEAH, THANKS.
- YEAH.

04:01.937 --> 04:04.940
WOMAN: ARE YOU A READER
OF OUR PUBLICATION?

04:04.983 --> 04:07.551
OLIVIA: YES, FOR AS LONG
AS I CAN REMEMBER.

04:07.595 --> 04:10.902
UM, MY PARENTS STILL GET
THE NEWSPAPER EDITION...
WOMAN: MMM.

04:10.946 --> 04:14.602
AND I READ THE ONLINE SITE,
WHICH IS, YOU KNOW,
PRETTY MUCH WHY I'M HERE.

04:14.645 --> 04:16.995
SO WHAT CAN WE
DO BETTER?

04:17.039 --> 04:18.910
UH, UM...NOTHING,

04:18.954 --> 04:20.911
I THINK IT'S GREAT.

04:20.956 --> 04:22.914
GOOD TO KNOW.

04:22.958 --> 04:25.308
SO WHY WOULD WE
NEED YOUR HELP,

04:25.352 --> 04:27.919
IF WE'RE
ALREADY PERFECT?

04:27.963 --> 04:31.009
UM, WELL...

04:32.533 --> 04:34.491
[CHUCKLES]

04:34.535 --> 04:36.667
THAT QUESTION STUMPS EVERYONE.
[OLIVIA CHUCKLES]

04:36.711 --> 04:39.061
IT'S A BIT UNFAIR,
PUTTING YOU ON
THE SPOT LIKE THAT.

04:39.104 --> 04:41.281
WE ASK IT
TO CHALLENGE
EACH APPLICANT

04:41.324 --> 04:43.457
TO SPEAK UP,
BUT THAT'S
A RARE QUALITY

04:43.500 --> 04:45.807
WE ALREADY KNOW
YOU POSSESS.

04:45.850 --> 04:47.809
- REALLY?
- I WAS IMPRESSED
WITH YOUR PODCAST.

04:47.852 --> 04:49.854
- OH, YOU LISTENED TO IT?
- MM-HMM.

04:49.898 --> 04:52.074
THANK YOU.
YEAH, I WAS JUST TRYING

04:52.117 --> 04:54.468
TO GIVE A SMALL VOICE
TO THOSE AFFECTED
BY INJUSTICES.

04:54.511 --> 04:56.470
WELL, I'D SAY YOU
GAVE THEM A BIG VOICE.

04:56.513 --> 04:59.124
ANYWAY, WHILE I AM
THRILLED TO KNOW
YOU THINK

04:59.168 --> 05:01.518
THE "L.A. TRIBUNE IS
PERFECT THE WAY IT IS,

05:01.562 --> 05:03.868
I AM ALWAYS LOOKING
FOR WAYS TO IMPROVE,

05:03.912 --> 05:06.349
NEW VOICES,
LIKE YOURS.

05:06.393 --> 05:08.569
AND IT'S BEEN
A HEAVY COUPLE YEARS.

05:08.612 --> 05:11.572
PEOPLE ARE EXHAUSTED,
SO I'D LIKE TO START

05:11.615 --> 05:14.966
BALANCING OUR STORIES
WITH SOME...
LIGHTER TOPICS.

05:15.010 --> 05:17.969
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.
UM, I'M PERSONALLY TRYING

05:18.013 --> 05:22.539
TO EMBRACE MORE LIGHT
THIS YEAR, YOU KNOW,
LEAN INTO THE JOY.

05:22.583 --> 05:26.195
THEN THAT'S PERFECT.
SEE, WE ALREADY KNOW
THAT YOU ARE MORE

05:26.238 --> 05:28.589
THAN CAPABLE OF
HARDER-HITTING PIECES.

05:28.632 --> 05:30.591
NOW WE'D LIKE TO SEE
IF YOU CAN DELIVER
SOMETHING A BIT

05:30.634 --> 05:32.723
MORE...FUN AND POPPY,

05:32.767 --> 05:34.856
AN INSPIRING STORY.

05:34.899 --> 05:37.467
- ARE YOU GIVING ME
AN ASSIGNMENT?
- CONSIDER IT A TRYOUT.

05:37.511 --> 05:40.557
YOU THINK YOU CAN
DELIVER SOMETHING
IN TWO DAYS?

05:40.601 --> 05:43.560
YES, OF COURSE.
WHAT'S THE TOPIC?

05:43.604 --> 05:46.215
I WILL LEAVE THAT
UP TO YOU.

05:46.258 --> 05:48.435
JUST...
MAKE US SMILE.

05:48.478 --> 05:50.567
[CHUCKLES]
OK.

05:50.611 --> 05:53.048
MALE SINGER: ♪ WHAT A TIME
TO BE ALIVE, YEAH ♪

05:53.091 --> 05:56.660
YEAH, I GUESS I
DIDN'T REALIZE SHE
WAS SO ICE-COLD.

05:56.704 --> 06:00.098
- OH, OK, YOU'RE OVERREACTING.
- [SIGHS]

06:00.142 --> 06:02.492
WELL, YOU SHOULD HAVE
SEEN HER, LIKE, JUST

06:02.536 --> 06:04.886
BACK IN THE STUDIO,
BUSINESS AS USUAL.

06:04.929 --> 06:07.367
- WELL, WHAT DID
YOU EXPECT HER TO DO?
- WHY ARE YOU DEFENDING LAYLA?

06:07.410 --> 06:10.370
I'M NOT,
BUT, YOU KNOW, SHE'S
UNDER A LOT OF PRESSURE

06:10.413 --> 06:13.329
TO FINISH THESE TRACKS,
AND YOU JUST TOLD HER
THAT YOU COULDN'T DO IT.

06:13.373 --> 06:15.505
YOU KNOW, I HONESTLY
THOUGHT YOU'D BE ON MY SIDE
AFTER WHAT J.P. DID TO YOU.

06:15.549 --> 06:17.333
NO, THIS AIN'T
NOTHING LIKE THAT.

06:17.377 --> 06:19.248
J.P. CUT ME OUT
OF THE PROCESS.

06:19.291 --> 06:21.381
NOW, LAYLA WOULD
WELCOME YOUR INPUT,

06:21.424 --> 06:24.775
BUT YOU JUST TOLD HER
THAT YOU DON'T WANT TO BE
AROUND MUSIC ANYMORE.

06:24.819 --> 06:27.561
OR MAYBE I JUST
DON'T WANT TO HEAR ANOTHER
ARTIST BUTCHER MY LYRICS.

06:27.604 --> 06:29.563
LOOK, HER CAREER
IS ON THE LINE,

06:29.606 --> 06:32.392
AND YOU CAN'T JUST
EXPECT LAYLA TO GIVE UP.

06:37.353 --> 06:39.311
[EXHALES]

06:39.355 --> 06:42.184
THEY SAY CHAMPIONS ARE
MADE IN THE OFFSEASON.

06:42.227 --> 06:44.534
[CHUCKLES]
KEEP ON GRINDIN'.

06:44.578 --> 06:46.536
HEH!
WHAT'S UP, COACH?

06:46.580 --> 06:48.190
HEH HEH HEH!
WAIT TILL YOU SEE

06:48.233 --> 06:50.453
OUR WEIGHT ROOM, MAN.
IT'S STATE-OF-THE-ART.

06:50.497 --> 06:53.456
COACH BAKER SAID IT DON'T
MATTER WHERE YOU SWEAT, JUST
AS LONG AS YOU GIVE 100.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.502
COACH BILLY'S
A GOOD COACH.

06:57.504 --> 06:59.157
THANK YOU.

06:59.201 --> 07:01.159
YEAH, SO WAS
COACH DANTE.

07:01.203 --> 07:03.771
YEP, AND WE WERE SORRY
TO SEE HIM GO.

07:03.814 --> 07:05.990
BUT DON'T YOU WORRY.
WE'RE GONNA FILL HIS SPOT

07:06.034 --> 07:08.210
WITH SOMEBODY
WHO'S TOP-NOTCH
WITH NFL EXPERIENCE.

07:08.253 --> 07:10.473
HEH! YOU'RE--YOU'RE
GONNA BE IN GOOD HANDS.

07:10.517 --> 07:12.910
OK. CAN I ASK YOU
A QUESTION?

07:12.954 --> 07:14.564
ALWAYS.

07:14.608 --> 07:16.566
DID YOU KNOW
COACH DANTE
WAS LEAVING

07:16.610 --> 07:18.220
WHEN I SIGNED
MY LETTER
OF INTENT?

07:18.263 --> 07:20.265
- YES.
- AND HOW COME NOBODY TOLD ME?

07:20.309 --> 07:23.486
I WAS UNDER THE IMPRESSION
THAT YOU WERE...

07:23.530 --> 07:26.097
COMMITTED TO THE SCHOOL,
THE TRADITION,

07:26.141 --> 07:28.491
THE TOP-25 PROGRAM,
OR WAS I MISTAKEN?

07:28.535 --> 07:31.712
WERE YOU...COMMITTING
TO AN ASSISTANT COACH?

07:31.755 --> 07:33.365
NO.

07:33.409 --> 07:35.977
I MEAN...

07:36.020 --> 07:37.979
MAYBE ALL OF IT.

07:38.022 --> 07:41.591
SPENCER, I ASSURE YOU
YOU ARE THE JEWEL IN
OUR RECRUITMENT CLASS.

07:41.635 --> 07:43.811
YOU ARE THE NUMBER-ONE
PRIORITY.

07:43.854 --> 07:47.815
I CAME OUT HERE TO SEE
YOU PLAY IN THE PLATINUM
ALL-AMERICAN GAME.

07:47.858 --> 07:50.208
I THOUGHT YOU'D
BE GRATEFUL.

07:50.252 --> 07:52.472
GRATEFUL?

07:52.515 --> 07:57.085
THAT A POWER-5 TEAM
IS WILLING TO BUILD
ITS ENTIRE OFFENSE

07:57.128 --> 08:00.001
AROUND A FRESHMAN
NAMED SPENCER JAMES.

08:00.044 --> 08:01.524
I AM.

08:01.568 --> 08:03.178
- GOOD!
- YES, SIR.

08:03.221 --> 08:05.180
BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
NOT EVERYBODY GETS

08:05.223 --> 08:07.922
THE GOLDEN OPPORTUNITY
WE'RE GIVING YOU
AT TOLEDO STATE.

08:07.965 --> 08:10.011
REMEMBER THAT.

08:14.711 --> 08:16.713
[KNOCK ON DOOR, DOOR OPENS]

08:16.757 --> 08:18.846
ALREADY WORKING
ON YOUR PLAYBOOK
FOR NEXT SEASON?

08:18.889 --> 08:20.500
HA HA HA! COACH.

08:20.543 --> 08:22.197
YOU'RE A LONG WAY
FROM OHIO.

08:22.240 --> 08:24.199
HAD TO COME OUT AND SEE
MY STAR RECRUIT

08:24.242 --> 08:26.114
PLAY IN THE PLATINUM
ALL-AMERICAN GAME.
BILLY: HA HA!

08:26.157 --> 08:28.725
DRAWING UP PLAYS
FOR THAT VERY GAME.

08:28.769 --> 08:31.423
TRYING TO KEEP IT SIMPLE,
INVOLVE EVERYBODY.

08:31.467 --> 08:33.469
GONNA BE A LOT
OF EGOS OUT THERE
ON THAT FIELD.

08:33.513 --> 08:35.515
WELL, I'M GLAD I
SIGNED ONE OF 'EM.

08:35.558 --> 08:37.125
NO, NO, NOT SPENCER.

08:37.168 --> 08:39.256
HE IS A TEAM PLAYER
ALL THE WAY.

08:39.301 --> 08:41.563
YOU GOT
A GREAT YOUNG MAN
ON YOUR HANDS.

08:41.607 --> 08:46.395
I'VE BEEN LUCKY, LUCKY
TO, UH, COACH HIM FOR
THE PAST TWO YEARS.

08:46.438 --> 08:49.485
YOU WANT TO KEEP
THAT RELATIONSHIP GOING?

08:52.140 --> 08:54.098
ARE YOU
OFFERING ME A JOB?

08:54.142 --> 08:56.100
WIDE RECEIVER COACH.

08:56.144 --> 08:58.015
POSITION JUST OPENED UP.

08:58.059 --> 09:00.235
YEAH, I HAD HEARD.

09:00.278 --> 09:03.151
COACH DANTE DID
A REALLY GOOD JOB
AT RECRUITING SPENCER.

09:03.194 --> 09:06.154
ARE YOU OFFERING ME
THIS JOB TO MAKE SURE
SPENCER STAYS COMMITTED?

09:06.197 --> 09:09.157
SPENCER'S SIGNED,
HE'S NOT COMMITTED.

09:09.200 --> 09:11.159
I'M OFFERING YOU THE JOB
BECAUSE YOU'RE ONE OF

09:11.202 --> 09:13.248
THE BEST HIGH SCHOOL
COACHES IN AMERICA,

09:13.291 --> 09:15.859
AND I THINK YOU'RE READY
TO TAKE THE NEXT STEP.
DO YOU THINK YOU ARE?

09:15.903 --> 09:19.863
AH, POWER-5.
HONESTLY, I HAVEN'T--I
HAVEN'T EVEN CONSIDERED--

09:19.907 --> 09:24.041
SURE, YOU HAVE.
I'VE FOLLOWED YOUR CAREER
SINCE YOU LEFT THE NFL.

09:24.085 --> 09:26.261
SEAMLESSLY TRANSITIONED
INTO COACHING,

09:26.304 --> 09:29.612
NOW TWO BACK-TO-BACK
STATE CHAMPIONSHIP GAMES.

09:29.656 --> 09:31.614
IT'S CLEAR
YOU'RE A WINNER.

09:31.658 --> 09:34.878
WELL, THANKS, COACH,
AND I APPRECIATE THAT.

09:34.922 --> 09:38.882
UH...WOW.
CAN I THINK ABOUT IT,
TALK TO THE WIFE?

09:38.926 --> 09:41.581
- SURE. JUST LET ME
KNOW AT THE GAME.
- ALL RIGHT.

09:41.624 --> 09:45.715
UH, WHILE I CONSIDER,
LET'S NOT TELL SPENCER.

09:45.759 --> 09:47.978
GOOD LUCK
ON THOSE PLAYS.

09:48.022 --> 09:50.677
ALL RIGHT.
THANKS, COACH.

09:58.336 --> 10:00.687
SIMONE: LOOK AT
YOUR LITTLE RECORDER

10:00.730 --> 10:02.558
[CHUCKLING]
AND CUTE LITTLE NOTEPAD.

10:02.602 --> 10:04.168
THIS IS CUTE.

10:04.212 --> 10:06.388
YOU KNOW, I'M TRYING
TO BE PROFESSIONAL.

10:06.431 --> 10:08.999
WELL, THEN, WELL, THEN,
WHAT IS THIS ASSIGNMENT?

10:09.043 --> 10:13.003
IT'S BASICALLY A TRYOUT
FOR A SUMMER JOB AT THE
"L.A. TRIBUNE" ONLINE.

10:13.047 --> 10:16.659
YOU KNOW, THEY LIKE ME.
THEY JUST WANT TO SEE
IF I CAN DELIVER

10:16.703 --> 10:19.140
A FUN, POPPY,
UPLIFTING STORY.

10:19.183 --> 10:21.098
POPPY? YOU?

10:21.142 --> 10:22.665
I CAN BE POPPY.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.319
GIRL, YOU ARE
THE POSTER CHILD

10:24.362 --> 10:26.408
FOR BLACK EMO CHICK,
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

10:26.451 --> 10:28.628
LET'S JUST GIVE IT
A SHOT ANYWAY, HMM?

10:28.671 --> 10:30.673
SO, WHAT'S THE TOPIC?

10:30.717 --> 10:32.675
WELL, THEY LET ME
PICK THAT MYSELF,

10:32.719 --> 10:35.591
AND I DECIDED
ON BLACK EXCELLENCE.

10:35.635 --> 10:38.202
SO YOU'RE
INTERVIEWING ME?

10:38.246 --> 10:40.727
OF COURSE I AM.
READY?

10:40.770 --> 10:43.120
[TURNS ON,
SETS DOWN RECORDER]

10:44.948 --> 10:48.082
TELL ME ABOUT
YOUR DECISION TO ATTEND
BRINGSTON UNIVERSITY.

10:48.125 --> 10:52.086
WELL, MY WHOLE LIFE,
I WANTED TO GO
TO PRINCETON

10:52.129 --> 10:55.089
BECAUSE I THOUGHT
ATTENDING AN IVY WAS

10:55.132 --> 10:58.005
THE EPITOME
OF BLACK EXCELLENCE,

10:58.048 --> 11:01.965
YOU KNOW,
LIKE A BADGE OF HONOR,
BUT THEN I REALIZED

11:02.009 --> 11:04.968
BRINGSTON WAS
A VERY DIFFERENT VERSION
OF BLACK EXCELLENCE,

11:05.012 --> 11:07.667
ONE THAT DIDN'T COME
WITH THAT BURDEN.

11:07.710 --> 11:09.669
- WHAT BURDEN?
- WELL, BLACK ATHLETES HAVE

11:09.712 --> 11:11.845
UNREALISTIC EXPECTATIONS
PUT ON THEM.

11:11.888 --> 11:15.500
THERE'S ALWAYS
THIS...PRESSURE
TO BE PERFECT.

11:15.544 --> 11:17.154
CAN YOU GIVE ME
AN EXAMPLE?

11:17.198 --> 11:19.156
GIRL, DID YOU WATCH
THE OLYMPICS?

11:19.200 --> 11:21.724
TAKE SIMONE BILES
OR EVEN TIGER WOODS.

11:21.768 --> 11:24.727
PEOPLE ARE JUST WAITING
TO TEAR YOU DOWN.

11:24.771 --> 11:28.383
WHEN I STARTED PLAYING
TENNIS AGAIN, I...

11:28.426 --> 11:31.386
I DIDN'T TELL MY COACH
THAT IN MY YEAR OFF,

11:31.429 --> 11:34.389
I HAD GOTTEN PREGNANT.

11:34.432 --> 11:38.001
I HID IT FROM
MY JUNIOR TENNIS LEAGUE...

11:38.045 --> 11:42.092
BECAUSE I DIDN'T
WANT THEM TO SEE ME
AS LESS THAN PERFECT.

11:43.703 --> 11:46.270
AND AT BRINGSTON,

11:46.314 --> 11:50.710
BEING GREAT IS--
IS A JOURNEY.

11:50.753 --> 11:53.538
YOU GET TO DO YOU,
SO I CAN MAKE MISTAKES

11:53.582 --> 11:55.758
AND STILL BE GREAT.

12:00.241 --> 12:02.199
[SETS DOWN PEN]

12:02.243 --> 12:04.201
BILLY: HEY.
YOU HEADED OUT?

12:04.245 --> 12:06.421
YEAH. I'M ON MY WAY
TO MEET LIV.

12:06.464 --> 12:08.640
SHE WANT TO
INTERVIEW ME FOR THIS
ASSIGNMENT SHE DOING.

12:08.684 --> 12:11.643
OK, COOL. WELL, SEE YOU
AT PRACTICE TOMORROW.

12:11.687 --> 12:14.603
- HEY, CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?
- YEAH.

12:14.646 --> 12:17.737
WHEN YOU WERE PICKING
YOUR COLLEGE, DID YOU CHOOSE
THE COACH OR THE SCHOOL?

12:17.780 --> 12:20.740
I CHOSE THE SCHOOL.

12:20.783 --> 12:23.655
YEAH, I THINK
THE COACH THAT
RECRUITED ME WAS GONE

12:23.699 --> 12:25.657
BY MY SOPHOMORE YEAR
OR SOMETHING.

12:25.701 --> 12:28.660
- HMM.
- IS THIS ABOUT
COACH DANTE LEAVING TOLEDO?

12:28.704 --> 12:32.664
KINDA. I'M TRYING
TO FIGURE OUT WHY I
CHOSE TOLEDO STATE.

12:32.708 --> 12:34.666
WELL,
WHAT'S YOUR ANSWER?

12:34.710 --> 12:36.843
BOTH, I THINK.

12:36.886 --> 12:39.280
I MEAN, I--I DEFINITELY
WANTED TO PLAY FOR HIM.
BILLY: RIGHT.

12:39.323 --> 12:43.284
I LIKE HAVING A CONNECTION
TO MY COACH, JUST LIKE HOW
I FOLLOWED YOU TO BEVERLY,

12:43.327 --> 12:46.069
AND THEN WE CAME
BACK HERE TOGETHER,

12:46.113 --> 12:49.290
BUT THAT SCHOOL, MAN,
THAT IS EVERYTHING I WANT.

12:49.333 --> 12:51.771
- YEAH.
- THAT STADIUM, THE FANS,

12:51.814 --> 12:53.816
I'D BE ON NATIONAL TV
EVERY WEEK.

12:53.860 --> 12:57.428
PLUS, COACH HUDSON,
YOU KNOW, HE SENDS A LOT
OF PLAYERS TO THE NFL.

12:57.472 --> 12:59.039
YEAH.

12:59.082 --> 13:01.476
I MEAN, I KNOW IT'S
A GREAT OPPORTUNITY FOR ME,

13:01.519 --> 13:04.479
SO...WHY AM I DOUBTING IT
ALL OF A SUDDEN?

13:04.522 --> 13:08.135
LOOK, MAN, THIS IS
THE SINGLE BIGGEST
DECISION YOU'VE EVER MADE.

13:08.178 --> 13:11.747
I'D JUST SAY FOLLOW
YOUR INSTINCTS,
FOLLOW YOUR GUT.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.836
YOU'LL FIGURE IT OUT.
SPENCER: YEAH.

13:13.880 --> 13:15.620
[FOOTSTEPS RETREAT]

13:18.188 --> 13:20.147
- HEY.
- HEY.

13:20.190 --> 13:22.149
[KISS]
SPENCER: SORRY I'M LATE.

13:22.192 --> 13:24.847
- AH, I JUST FINISHED
UP WITH SIMONE.
- HOW'D THAT GO?

13:24.891 --> 13:27.850
SIMONE WAS GREAT.
UM, YOU KNOW, SHE HAS

13:27.894 --> 13:30.505
SUCH A STRONG POINT
OF VIEW. IT JUST...

13:30.548 --> 13:32.507
IT JUST WASN'T
THE ASSIGNMENT
THAT I WAS GIVEN.

13:32.550 --> 13:34.770
- WHICH IS?
- POPPY.

13:34.814 --> 13:37.381
- POPPY?
- POPPY AND FUN,

13:37.425 --> 13:40.689
WHICH, SIMONE'S
INTERVIEW GOT
PRETTY SERIOUS...

13:40.732 --> 13:42.691
- HMM.
- AND, YOU KNOW, THEY'VE

13:42.734 --> 13:45.172
ALREADY SEEN THAT SIDE
OF ME FROM MY PODCAST.

13:45.215 --> 13:48.392
YOU KNOW, I WANT
TO PROVE TO THEM
THAT I HAVE SOME RANGE.

13:48.436 --> 13:50.394
- SO THE PRESSURE'S ON ME?
- BIG TIME.

13:50.438 --> 13:52.788
- I GOT TO BRING THE FUN?
- YEAH, JUST BE

13:52.832 --> 13:54.790
UPLIFTING AND INSPIRING.

13:54.834 --> 13:57.184
AND POPPY.
GOT IT. HEH HEH!

13:59.186 --> 14:02.232
[SETS DOWN RECORDER]
OK.

14:03.843 --> 14:06.410
TELL ME WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO GET A FULL SCHOLARSHIP

14:06.454 --> 14:09.022
TO PLAY FOOTBALL
AT A MAJOR
DIVISION-1 SCHOOL.

14:09.065 --> 14:11.676
IT IS A DREAM COME TRUE.

14:11.720 --> 14:15.289
CAN'T BELIEVE I'M GONNA
BE SCORING TOUCHDOWNS
ON NATIONAL TV NEXT YEAR.

14:15.332 --> 14:17.726
[BOTH CHUCKLE]
SPENCER: AND CONSIDERING WHERE

14:17.769 --> 14:19.989
I CAME FROM,
I'M JUST GRATEFUL
FOR THE OPPORTUNITY.

14:20.033 --> 14:22.774
OOH, THIS IS GOOD STUFF.
KEEP IT GOING.

14:22.818 --> 14:27.170
OK, UH...I THINK
THE HEAD COACH AT TOLEDO STATE
WISHES I WAS MORE GRATEFUL,

14:27.214 --> 14:29.869
BUT, UM--
OLIVIA: WHAT MAKES YOU SAY THAT?

14:29.912 --> 14:32.480
WELL, WHEN I QUESTIONED HIM
ABOUT COACH DANTE LEAVING,

14:32.523 --> 14:36.136
HE SAID...HE THOUGHT
I'D BE MORE GRATEFUL.

14:36.179 --> 14:38.790
BUT HE'S RIGHT, YOU KNOW,
WITH THE OPPORTUNITY

14:38.834 --> 14:41.184
THEY'VE GIVEN ME...

14:41.228 --> 14:43.970
I GUESS...I DON'T KNOW.
OLIVIA: UM,

14:44.013 --> 14:45.623
PAUSE.

14:45.667 --> 14:47.625
HELL NO.

14:47.669 --> 14:51.238
HE'S GASLIGHTING YOU.
HE'S MAKING YOU FEEL BAD
FOR ASKING

14:51.281 --> 14:54.328
A SIMPLE QUESTION,
ALL BECAUSE THE ANSWER
MIGHT MAKE HIM LOOK BAD.

14:54.371 --> 14:56.939
BUT I AM GRATEFUL.
I AIN'T HAD THAT MANY OFFERS

14:56.983 --> 14:58.941
FROM ANY OF THE OTHER
BIG-TIME SCHOOLS,

14:58.985 --> 15:01.988
AND AFTER I GOT SHOT,
A LOT OF THOSE SCHOOLS
BACKED OFF.

15:02.031 --> 15:04.991
ONCE I WAS HEALED,
IT AIN'T LIKE THEY
CAME POURING BACK IN.

15:05.034 --> 15:06.906
- BECAUSE YOU WEREN'T PERFECT.
- WHAT?

15:06.949 --> 15:08.908
I THINK YOU'RE PERFECT,

15:08.951 --> 15:12.737
BUT...I MEAN, SIMONE
WAS JUST TALKING

15:12.781 --> 15:15.740
ABOUT THIS BURDEN
THAT BLACK ATHLETES FACE

15:15.784 --> 15:17.960
AND HOW THEY'RE HELD
TO THIS HIGHER STANDARD,

15:18.004 --> 15:20.136
AND IT SOUNDS LIKE YOU
NEED TO BE PERFECT...

15:20.180 --> 15:22.530
OR I AIN'T WORTH
THE TROUBLE.

15:22.573 --> 15:24.532
[SIGHS]
MY BAD.

15:24.575 --> 15:27.535
I'M NOT BRINGING THE FUN.
UM...COME ON.

15:27.578 --> 15:30.842
ASK ME A POPPY QUESTION,
AND I WILL GIVE YOU
A POPPY ANSWER.

15:30.886 --> 15:32.844
IT'S OK.

15:32.888 --> 15:35.935
THE TRUTH IS
MORE IMPORTANT
THAN THE FUN.

15:41.723 --> 15:43.681
BABY.

15:43.725 --> 15:46.684
WHEN WAS
THE LAST TIME...

15:46.728 --> 15:48.817
YOU WERE IN OHIO?

15:48.860 --> 15:51.689
I THINK WHEN YOU
PLAYED CLEVELAND,

15:51.733 --> 15:53.735
OR WAS IT CINCINNATI?
BILLY: YEAH, THAT WAS CLEVELAND.

15:53.778 --> 15:55.737
YEAH, DON'T REMIND ME.
[SCOFFS]

15:55.780 --> 15:58.522
AND YOU FUMBLED
IN THE FOURTH QUARTER

15:58.566 --> 16:00.524
AND LOST THE GAME.

16:00.568 --> 16:04.180
- DIDN'T I TELL YOU NOT TO--
- OK, SORRY. YOU BROUGHT IT UP.

16:04.224 --> 16:06.835
- YOU EVER BEEN IN TOLEDO?
- NO, BUT, UH,

16:06.878 --> 16:09.838
I PROMISED THAT WE'D GO
FOR SPENCER'S FIRST GAME.

16:09.881 --> 16:12.232
OK, WELL,
WHAT IF WE WENT

16:12.275 --> 16:14.234
FOR SPENCER'S
FIRST GAME

16:14.277 --> 16:17.324
AND THEN...STAYED?

16:20.283 --> 16:22.894
- UM...
- THE, UH,

16:22.938 --> 16:26.376
THE HEAD COACH
FROM TOLEDO STATE
OFFERED ME A JOB--

16:26.420 --> 16:29.031
WIDE RECEIVERS COACH.

16:29.075 --> 16:31.903
AND WE'D LIVE IN OHIO?

16:31.947 --> 16:33.905
YEAH. IS THAT
A DEAL-BREAKER?

16:33.949 --> 16:36.734
I'M JUST PROCESSING
THIS NEW INFORMATION.

16:36.778 --> 16:38.736
YEAH.

16:38.780 --> 16:40.738
BUT...

16:40.782 --> 16:42.740
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN MY CAREER,

16:42.784 --> 16:46.353
I'M...FREE
TO MOVE ANYWHERE,

16:46.396 --> 16:49.008
SO I GUESS...

16:49.051 --> 16:53.012
THE QUESTION IS,
AND BE HONEST,

16:53.055 --> 16:55.449
DO YOU WANT THIS JOB?

16:58.104 --> 17:02.151
YEAH...I THINK I DO.

17:05.720 --> 17:07.287
SIMONE ON RECORDING:
WELL, MY WHOLE LIFE,

17:07.329 --> 17:09.941
I WANTED TO GO TO PRINCETON
BECAUSE I THOUGHT ATTENDING...

17:09.984 --> 17:11.813
- [SIGHS] IS THAT SIMONE?
- YUP.

17:11.856 --> 17:13.902
WELL, YOU KNOW YOU
COULD HAVE ASKED ME,
RIGHT?

17:13.944 --> 17:16.512
I DON'T NEED
YOUR PERMISSION
TO TALK TO SIMONE.

17:16.557 --> 17:19.125
NO, I MEANT YOU COULD
HAVE ASKED TO INTERVIEW
ME FOR YOUR PROJECT,

17:19.167 --> 17:21.561
OR AM I NOT AN EXAMPLE
OF BLACK EXCELLENCE?

17:21.605 --> 17:23.172
DON'T TAKE IT
PERSONALLY, JORDAN, OK?

17:23.215 --> 17:24.826
I JUST THOUGHT
THAT SIMONE AND SPENCER

17:24.868 --> 17:26.306
WOULD HAVE INTERESTING
POINT OF VIEWS.

17:26.348 --> 17:28.743
[SCOFFS]
OK, SO YOU ASKED
SPENCER AS WELL.

17:28.786 --> 17:31.789
IF IT MAKES YOU FEEL
ANY BETTER, THE PROJECT
ISN'T GOING VERY WELL.

17:31.833 --> 17:34.009
NICE.
[THUMPS COUNTER]

17:34.053 --> 17:36.838
[SIGHS]
WHY DOES NOBODY
SEE ME AS GREAT?

17:36.881 --> 17:39.449
- JORDAN.
- NO, NO, I'M SERIOUS, LIV.

17:39.493 --> 17:42.626
LOOK, COLLEGE COACHES
OBVIOUSLY DON'T
SEE ME AS GREAT.

17:42.670 --> 17:44.628
MY OWN SISTER DOESN'T
EVEN SEE ME AS GREAT.

17:44.672 --> 17:46.456
YES, I DO.

17:46.500 --> 17:49.677
IT'S JUST THAT
SOMETIMES YOU DON'T
SEE YOURSELF THAT WAY,

17:49.720 --> 17:52.027
AND THAT AFFECTS HOW
OTHER PEOPLE SEE YOU.

17:52.071 --> 17:55.030
NO, MAYBE I USED TO
DOUBT MYSELF, ALL RIGHT,
BUT NOT ANYMORE.

17:55.074 --> 17:57.424
LOOK, I KNOW THAT I CAN
GREAT, OLIVIA.

17:57.467 --> 17:59.643
IT'S JUST THAT NOBODY
ELSE WANTS TO SEE IT.

17:59.687 --> 18:01.341
WELL, THEN CHANGE THE WAY
THAT PEOPLE SEE YOU.

18:01.384 --> 18:03.734
- HOW?
- BY BEING GREAT.

18:05.432 --> 18:08.348
[MALE SINGERS VOCALIZE]

18:08.391 --> 18:10.350
SPENCER JAMES,

18:10.393 --> 18:12.134
ALL-AMERICAN.

18:12.178 --> 18:14.658
CAM. I HEARD YOU
GOT THE INVITE.

18:14.702 --> 18:17.270
YEAH, MAN. BACK ON
THE SAME TEAM AGAIN.

18:17.313 --> 18:19.707
- YEP.
- HEY, YO, WE'D BETTER
SMOKE THESE FOOLS TOMORROW.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.709
IT'S JUST
AN EXHIBITION
GAME, MAN.

18:21.752 --> 18:23.711
I DON'T THINK
THE SCORE
REALLY MATTERS.

18:23.754 --> 18:26.409
WE'RE JUST HERE
TO SHOWCASE OUR
TALENTS, YOU KNOW?

18:26.453 --> 18:30.500
ONLY THING
THAT DUDE'S SHOWCASING
IS THAT BIG-ASS HEAD.

18:32.285 --> 18:34.113
WHAT DID YOU JUST SAY?

18:34.156 --> 18:36.115
YO, HEY, HEY,
CHILL, CHILL.

18:36.158 --> 18:38.421
HE AIN'T SAY
NOTHIN'.

18:44.340 --> 18:46.951
WHY YOU GOTTA
RUN YOUR MOUTH
TO EVERYBODY, MAN?

18:46.995 --> 18:50.172
I GET THAT'S YOUR THING,
BUT THAT IS A 5-STAR
LINEBACKER OUTTA TEXAS.

18:50.216 --> 18:52.174
HE WILL BREAK YOU
IN HALF.

18:52.218 --> 18:55.569
- HE DID HAVE A BIG-ASS
HEAD, THOUGH, RIGHT?
- HUGE.

18:55.612 --> 18:58.224
- THAT'S ALL I'M SAYIN'.
- [CHUCKLING] GO, MAN.

19:00.704 --> 19:02.663
[DISTANT SHOUTING]

19:02.706 --> 19:05.361
KENT: YO, WE NEED
ANOTHER BALL OUT HERE!

19:09.800 --> 19:11.976
- BOOM.
- [WHISTLES] WHOO!

19:13.848 --> 19:16.416
- NICE TOSS.
- THANKS.

19:16.459 --> 19:18.418
PROBABLY
THE ONLY ONE
I'LL THROW TODAY.

19:18.461 --> 19:19.941
- RESERVE?
- YEAH.

19:19.984 --> 19:22.335
HEY, ME, TOO.
ISAIAH WINFIELD, ARIZONA.

19:22.378 --> 19:24.337
JORDAN BAKER
FROM RIGHT HERE.

19:24.380 --> 19:26.382
- OH, OK. CALI BOY.
- YEAH.

19:26.426 --> 19:28.384
YO, THERE'S SOME
SERIOUS TALENT ON
THIS FIELD, HUH?

19:28.428 --> 19:30.038
- MAN, BEST IN THE COUNTRY.
- YEAH.

19:30.081 --> 19:32.040
AND THAT INCLUDES US.
HEY, WHETHER WE GET

19:32.083 --> 19:34.042
INTO THAT GAME OR NOT,
WE STILL GET TO PUT ON

19:34.085 --> 19:36.740
THE SAME UNIFORMS AS THEM,
SAYS "ALL-AMERICAN"
ACROSS THE FRONT.

19:36.784 --> 19:38.916
HUH.

19:38.960 --> 19:41.528
IT SURE WOULD BE NICE
TO COMPETE AGAINST
THEM, THOUGH, RIGHT?

19:41.571 --> 19:44.183
YEAH. HEY, THAT DUDE
RIGHT THERE IS GOING
TO 'BAMA,

19:44.226 --> 19:46.794
THAT DUDE'S FLORIDA.
HE'S OREGON.

19:46.837 --> 19:48.796
WOW.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

19:48.839 --> 19:51.581
UNDECIDED. STILL TRYING
TO FIND THE RIGHT FIT
FOR ME, YOU KNOW?

19:51.625 --> 19:53.583
- RIGHT.
- HOW 'BOUT YOU?

19:53.627 --> 19:56.325
JUCO FOR A COUPLE YEARS
AND THEN TRANSFER INTO D1.

19:56.369 --> 19:58.588
- HEY, JUCO ROUTE'S STILL LEGIT.
- MM-HMM.

19:58.632 --> 20:01.417
- GRADES?
- TWO CONCUSSIONS.

20:06.030 --> 20:08.207
KIM NITTY, VOICE-OVER:
♪ NO QUESTIONS ASKED

20:08.250 --> 20:11.035
♪ I'M AT THE TOP, I JUST MIGHT
BUILD ME A HOUSE ON THE MOON ♪

20:11.079 --> 20:13.864
♪ YOU CAN TELL THAT I'M GREAT,
ONCE I'M DONE, I'M
GETTIN' TO IT ♪

20:13.908 --> 20:17.433
♪ I'LL KEEP ON MOVIN',
NEVER NO STOPPIN' ME,
I'M A BLAST ♪

20:17.477 --> 20:20.567
♪ NO QUESTIONS ASKED,
NO QUESTIONS ASKED ♪

20:20.610 --> 20:23.004
ASHER: LAYLA.
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

20:23.047 --> 20:26.007
- ASHER. WHAT UP, BRO?
- HEY, COOP.

20:26.050 --> 20:28.618
HEY, YOU, UH,
YOU SEEN LAYLA AROUND?

20:28.662 --> 20:32.840
ACTUALLY, NAH, MAN.
SHE'S GONE FOR THE DAY.
ONLY REASON I'M HERE.

20:32.883 --> 20:34.842
HARD TO STAY AWAY,
ISN'T IT?

20:34.885 --> 20:36.887
I KNOW EXACTLY
HOW IT FEELS.

20:36.931 --> 20:39.194
WE GOT A LOT
MORE IN COMMON
ALL OF A SUDDEN.

20:39.238 --> 20:42.937
WE WERE BOTH
LIVING OUR DREAMS,
AND IN A BLINK--

20:42.980 --> 20:45.548
IT WAS GONE.

20:45.592 --> 20:48.551
WHAT'S NEXT
FOR US, COOP?

20:48.595 --> 20:51.772
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.
I AM, UH,

20:51.815 --> 20:53.774
OBVIOUSLY SITTING
IN AN EMPTY STUDIO

20:53.817 --> 20:56.385
AFTER HOURS
BECAUSE I MISS IT.

20:56.429 --> 21:00.041
SO, UH...
THERE'S STEP ONE.

21:00.084 --> 21:03.349
DOES THAT MEAN I'LL
BE SITTING ON AN EMPTY
FOOTBALL FIELD SOON?

21:04.872 --> 21:06.787
- IT'S A START.
- YOU KNOW, HALF OF ME WANTS

21:06.830 --> 21:09.616
TO GO TO THAT GAME
BECAUSE JORDAN AND
SPENCER ARE BOTH IN IT,

21:09.659 --> 21:13.315
BUT...THE OTHER HALF
OF ME...

21:14.925 --> 21:19.452
IT'S TOO HARD.
YOU WANT TO BE
THE TIE-BREAKER FOR ME?

21:19.495 --> 21:23.107
I'D SAY COME
TO THE GAME, BRO.
SUPPORT YOUR BOYS.

21:23.151 --> 21:25.501
AIN'T LIKE YOU GOT
TO SIT AND LISTEN

21:25.545 --> 21:27.808
TO SOMEONE ELSE
SING YOUR SONG.

21:27.851 --> 21:30.419
YOU KNOW, FOR WHAT
IT'S WORTH, COOP, UM,

21:30.463 --> 21:33.422
IF SOMEONE WAS SINGING
A SONG THAT I WROTE,

21:33.466 --> 21:35.642
IT PROBABLY MEANS I WROTE
A DAMN GOOD SONG,

21:35.685 --> 21:38.297
SO I'D BE PROUD
TO LISTEN TO THAT.

21:41.256 --> 21:43.214
KENT: THAT'S ME,
THAT'S ME. COME ON.

21:43.258 --> 21:45.782
YEAH.
YOU REMEMBER ME, RIGHT?

21:45.826 --> 21:47.393
I REMEMBER
THAT BIG-ASS HEAD.

21:47.436 --> 21:49.090
THAT HELMET
CUSTOM-MADE FOR IT?

21:49.133 --> 21:51.048
REMEMBER YOU SAID THAT.

21:51.092 --> 21:52.659
TYRONE BRIGGS:
♪ TAKIN' OVER THE GAME

21:52.702 --> 21:54.095
♪ LIKE I'M SUPPOSED TO DO

21:54.138 --> 21:55.705
♪ FEEL THAT CROWD ENERGY

21:55.749 --> 21:57.533
♪ YOU CAN GO ASSUME
THIS GAME OVER ♪

21:57.577 --> 21:59.361
♪ GO BLOW THE TUNE,
DO IT FOR THE WHOLE TOWN ♪

21:59.405 --> 22:01.015
♪ THEY GOTTA LOVE IT
SINGER: ♪ HEY!

22:01.058 --> 22:02.930
BRIGGS: ♪ GO AHEAD,
BLOW THE TRUMPET ♪

22:02.973 --> 22:04.801
♪ LABEL ME THE GOAT,
Y'ALL CAN'T TELL ME NOTHING ♪

22:04.845 --> 22:06.803
- ♪ HEY!
- ♪ GO AHEAD, BLOW THE TRUMPET

22:06.847 --> 22:09.371
- ♪ HEY, HEY, HEY...
- ♪ BLOW THE TRUMPET

22:09.415 --> 22:12.026
YO, WHAT'S
YOUR PROBLEM, BRO?

22:12.069 --> 22:14.028
THIS IS PRACTICE
FOR AN ALL-STAR GAME.

22:14.071 --> 22:17.379
CAM: BRO, I PRACTICE
THE WAY I PLAY.

22:17.423 --> 22:20.034
- WHAT IS GOING ON OUT THERE?
- OH, IT'S JUST CAM BEING CAM.

22:20.077 --> 22:22.079
CAM: THIS SUPPOSED TO BE
THE BIG LEAGUES, DAWG.

22:22.123 --> 22:25.692
- THEN WHY ARE YOU HERE?
- I JUST SHOWED YOU
WHY I'M HERE.

22:25.735 --> 22:28.782
- WHAT SCHOOL YOU GOING TO?
- YOU'LL FIND OUT TOMORROW
AT HALFTIME.

22:28.825 --> 22:32.829
WHEREVER YOU END UP,
THEM SKINNY LEGS AIN'T
GONNA LAST ONE SEASON.

22:32.873 --> 22:35.266
PLAYER: HEY, HEY, HEY!
KENT: WHAT'S UP?
WANT TO DO THIS?

22:35.310 --> 22:37.399
YOU WANT TO DO THIS?
WE'LL DO THIS ALL DAY, BRO!

22:37.443 --> 22:39.967
PLAYER:
HEY, CALM DOWN! YO!

22:40.010 --> 22:42.839
JORDAN: HEY! HEY! HEY!
HEY, COME ON!

22:42.883 --> 22:45.189
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?
GUYS, STOP!

22:45.233 --> 22:49.324
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, FIGHTING
20 MINUTES INTO OUR ONLY
PRACTICE, OVER WHAT?

22:49.368 --> 22:52.980
WHO'S GOING TO THE BEST COLLEGE?
HOW MANY STARS YOU HAVE
NEXT TO YOUR NAME?

22:53.023 --> 22:56.244
YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE THE BEST PLAYERS IN
THE COUNTRY. ACT LIKE IT!

22:56.287 --> 22:58.638
YOU'RE ABOUT TO PLAY
IN A GAME CELEBRATING
HOW TALENTED YOU ALL ARE,

22:58.681 --> 23:02.206
HOW GREAT YOU ARE!
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE FUN!

23:02.250 --> 23:04.818
DROP YOUR EGOS
FOR ONE GAME

23:04.861 --> 23:07.647
AND SHAKE HANDS
AND KNOCK IT OFF!

23:07.690 --> 23:10.127
I SAID SHAKE HANDS, NOW!

23:13.392 --> 23:15.568
PLAY FOOTBALL.

23:15.611 --> 23:17.831
[BILLY CHUCKLES]

23:17.874 --> 23:20.442
HE GOT THAT FROM ME.

23:20.486 --> 23:23.532
NO. PRETTY SURE
HE GOT THAT FROM ME.

23:30.800 --> 23:32.367
YOU SHOULD HAVE
SEEN HIM, BABY.

23:32.411 --> 23:33.977
JORDAN WAS
IN COMPLETE CONTROL.

23:34.021 --> 23:35.588
HE WAS A LEADER.

23:35.631 --> 23:38.242
I HADN'T SEEN
THAT SIDE OF HIM.

23:38.286 --> 23:40.984
OH. I'VE SEEN GLIMPSES
OF IT THIS YEAR.

23:41.028 --> 23:42.986
HUH.

23:43.030 --> 23:45.424
I GUESS MONTES
HAS BEEN A REALLY
GOOD INFLUENCE ON HIM.

23:45.467 --> 23:50.037
WELL, SHE'S DEFINITELY
CHALLENGED HIM
TO STEP UP.

23:50.080 --> 23:52.039
YEAH.

23:52.082 --> 23:54.781
MAYBE SPENCER
NEEDS THAT.

23:54.824 --> 23:58.437
I'D HATE TO ROB HIM
OF A--OF A MENTOR,

23:58.480 --> 24:02.049
YOU KNOW, SOMEONE
WHO COULD BUILD ON WHAT
WE'VE WORKED ON TOGETHER.

24:02.092 --> 24:05.879
WAIT, ARE YOU--
ARE YOU BACKING OUT OF
THE TOLEDO STATE GIG?

24:05.922 --> 24:08.098
I MEAN,
MAYBE IT'S TIME

24:08.142 --> 24:11.101
FOR SPENCER
TO SPREAD HIS WINGS,

24:11.145 --> 24:13.103
YOU KNOW,
AND LET'S BE HONEST.

24:13.147 --> 24:16.542
ME TAKING THAT JOB,
YOU KNOW, WOULD
COMPLETELY UPROOT YOU--

24:16.585 --> 24:18.195
- DO NOT DO THAT.
- DO WHAT?

24:18.239 --> 24:20.197
DON'T MAKE
THIS DECISION

24:20.241 --> 24:22.809
ABOUT ME, OK?

24:22.852 --> 24:25.464
I AM SUPPORTING YOU.

24:25.507 --> 24:28.075
FOR THE FIRST HALF
OF OUR LIVES, YOU--
YOU SPENT LIVING

24:28.118 --> 24:30.991
IN MY WORLD, AND YOU
DID THAT FOR ME,

24:31.034 --> 24:33.123
FOR MY CAREER.

24:33.167 --> 24:36.387
I WILL FOLLOW YOU
WHEREVER YOU
WANT TO GO.

24:41.958 --> 24:44.526
ANNOUNCER: WELCOME
TO LOS ANGELES, CALIFORNIA,

24:44.570 --> 24:47.529
WHERE THE BEST HIGH SCHOOL
FOOTBALL PLAYERS IN THE COUNTRY

24:47.573 --> 24:49.531
HAVE GATHERED
TO SHOW OFF THEIR SKILLS

24:49.575 --> 24:51.751
IN THE PLATINUM
ALL-AMERICAN GAME.

24:51.794 --> 24:54.188
A NUMBER OF UNDECIDED
PROSPECTS WILL ANNOUNCE

24:54.231 --> 24:56.538
THEIR COLLEGE DECISIONS
AT HALFTIME.

24:56.582 --> 24:59.367
37 FORMER PLATINUM
ALL-AMERICANS WERE SELECTED

24:59.410 --> 25:01.761
IN THE FIRST ROUND
OF THE NFL DRAFT,

25:01.804 --> 25:03.719
SO THIS IS THE CREAM
OF THE CROP,

25:03.763 --> 25:05.373
THE FUTURE OF THE NFL.

25:05.416 --> 25:07.331
MALE SINGER:
♪ WE AIN'T THE SAME

25:07.375 --> 25:08.942
♪ NOT ONLY DEAL,
NOT ONLY NAME ♪

25:08.985 --> 25:10.552
BILLY: HEH HEH!

25:10.596 --> 25:12.467
WHAT YOU THINK ABOUT
THIS GUY RIGHT HERE?

25:12.511 --> 25:14.338
JORDAN: HE'S FROM ARKAN--
ISAIAH: YO, JORDAN.

25:14.382 --> 25:16.732
HEY, ISAIAH.
UH, WANT YOU
TO MEET MY DAD.

25:16.776 --> 25:19.735
- BILLY BAKER. IT'S AN HONOR.
- OK. GOOD TO MEET YOU,
YOUNG MAN.

25:19.779 --> 25:21.911
- THANK YOU. MY OLDER
BROTHER HAD YOUR JERSEY.
- OH, FOR REAL?

25:21.955 --> 25:24.044
WELL, TELL HIM I SAID HI.
ISAIAH: HEY, I WILL.

25:24.087 --> 25:26.133
IF HE NEEDS ME
TO SIGN IT OR ANYTHING,
I CAN DO THAT, TOO.

25:26.176 --> 25:29.658
OH, I DON'T THINK
HE HAS IT NO MORE.
THAT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

25:29.702 --> 25:32.661
- [CHUCKLES] AHEM!
- THE HELL YOU LAUGHIN' AT?

25:32.705 --> 25:35.316
JORDAN: I'M NOT.
I'M--I'M SORRY.

25:35.359 --> 25:37.927
BILLY: IT WAS GOOD
TO MEET YOU, ISAIAH.
ISAIAH: LIKEWISE.

25:37.971 --> 25:40.234
JORDAN:
SEE YOU OUT THERE.

25:40.277 --> 25:42.845
[LAUGHING]
YO, MAN,
THAT WAS CLASSIC.

25:42.889 --> 25:45.021
OH, YO, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOUR POPS WAS IN THE NFL.

25:45.065 --> 25:47.023
THAT'S THE DREAM, RIGHT?
JORDAN: IT'S COOL.

25:47.067 --> 25:49.025
I'M NOT GONNA LIE
TO YOU, THOUGH.

25:49.069 --> 25:51.027
IT HONESTLY WAS
TOUGH GROWING UP
IN HIS SHADOW.

25:51.071 --> 25:52.681
I MEAN EVERYTHING
I DID ON THE FIELD
WAS ALWAYS

25:52.725 --> 25:54.553
COMPARED TO HIM,
YOU KNOW? I MEAN,

25:54.596 --> 25:55.858
I ALMOST
QUIT FOOTBALL
A FEW TIMES.

25:55.902 --> 25:57.294
YEAH, BUT YOU DIDN'T,

25:57.338 --> 25:59.122
AND NOW LOOK WHERE
YOU'RE AT, AND BECAUSE

25:59.166 --> 26:01.211
YOU TOOK THAT PRESSURE
AND YOU TURNED IT
INTO FUEL, MAN.

26:01.255 --> 26:02.865
I DID.

26:02.909 --> 26:04.867
I TURNED IT
INTO FUEL.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

26:04.911 --> 26:06.521
COME ON.
LET'S WARM UP.

26:06.565 --> 26:08.436
OLIVIA, VOICE-OVER:
WHAT IS BLACK EXCELLENCE?

26:08.479 --> 26:10.307
THE EASY DEFINITION IS
IT'S CELEBRATING

26:10.351 --> 26:12.309
THE ACHIEVEMENTS
OF BLACK PEOPLE,

26:12.353 --> 26:15.312
BUT IS IT ATTAINABLE?
SOMETIMES BLACK EXCELLENCE COMES

26:15.356 --> 26:17.445
WITH AN UNREALISTIC BURDEN
ATTACHED TO IT.

26:17.488 --> 26:19.273
JUST LOOK
AT BLACK ATHLETES.

26:19.316 --> 26:21.623
THEY'RE CELEBRATED WHEN THEY
ACHIEVE GREATNESS,

26:21.667 --> 26:23.625
BUT JUST AS QUICKLY
TORN DOWN

26:23.669 --> 26:25.627
AT THE SLIGHTEST GLIMPSE
OF IMPERFECTION

26:25.671 --> 26:27.716
BECAUSE THEY'RE OFTEN SEEN
AS COMMODITIES.

26:27.760 --> 26:29.718
A BLACK FOOTBALL PLAYER
IS PRAISED

26:29.762 --> 26:31.720
AS LONG AS HE'S SCORING
TOUCHDOWNS,

26:31.764 --> 26:33.722
BUT ANY OFF-THE-FIELD MISTAKE,
AND THE NARRATIVE

26:33.766 --> 26:37.726
QUICKLY CHANGES TO "HE DOESN'T
REALLY DESERVE THIS OPPORTUNITY.

26:37.770 --> 26:41.164
DOESN'T HE KNOW HOW LUCKY HE IS
TO HAVE THIS OPPORTUNITY?"

26:41.208 --> 26:45.168
THIS BURDEN IS UNFAIR,
AND IT'S IMPOSSIBLE TO SUSTAIN,

26:45.212 --> 26:47.780
BUT IT'S BECOME INGRAINED
IN THE WORLD THAT WE LIVE IN.

26:47.823 --> 26:50.391
SPENCER: THAT'S WHAT I'M TALKIN'
'BOUT. JUST LIKE HOME, BABY.
CAM: JUST LIKE HOME, BABY.

26:50.434 --> 26:52.219
MALE SINGER: ♪ LIKE A TRAIN
COMIN', NO BRAKES ON ♪

26:52.262 --> 26:53.829
♪ CAN'T STOP ME,
YOU BETTER MOVE ♪

26:53.873 --> 26:55.657
♪ FEEL THE GROUND RUMBLE
LIKE A STAMPEDE ♪

26:55.701 --> 26:57.485
♪ WHEN I TAKE OFF,
I CAN'T LOSE ♪

26:57.528 --> 26:59.182
♪ I'M LIKE AN EARTHQUAKE
WITH MY HEART PUMPIN' ♪

26:59.226 --> 27:01.184
♪ I'M DIALED IN,
WE GONNA START SOMETHING ♪

27:01.228 --> 27:03.230
♪ WE GONNA LIGHT IT UP,
CAN'T SHUT US DOWN ♪

27:03.273 --> 27:05.145
♪ YOU HEAR THE THUNDER ROAR,
YOU KNOW THE STORM COMIN' ♪

27:05.188 --> 27:06.842
[WHISTLE BLOWS]
♪ YEAH, I ZERO IN
LIKE A PREDATOR ♪

27:06.886 --> 27:08.888
♪ AND YOU LOOKIN'
LIKE PREY ♪

27:08.931 --> 27:10.498
♪ GET READY FOR THE WAR ZONE
CAM: WHOO!

27:10.541 --> 27:12.543
OLIVIA, VOICE-OVER:
LET US MAKE MISTAKES

27:12.587 --> 27:16.156
WITHOUT IMMEDIATELY DECLARING,
"THEY DON'T DESERVE TO BE HERE,"

27:16.199 --> 27:18.680
AND LET US STRIVE FOR GREATNESS
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

27:18.724 --> 27:21.552
WITHOUT THAT IMPOSSIBLE BURDEN
OF PERFECTION.

27:21.596 --> 27:24.555
[CHUCKLES]
DAMN, I ALMOST
CAUGHT THAT, BRUH.

27:24.599 --> 27:26.166
YEAH, I KNOW, MAN.
HEH!

27:26.209 --> 27:27.776
HEY, YO, YOU
SEE ME BLOW PAST

27:27.820 --> 27:29.430
THAT BIG-HEADED
5-STAR FROM TEXAS?

27:29.473 --> 27:31.040
HEY, I'M NOT
GONNA LIE TO YOU.

27:31.084 --> 27:32.694
I WOULDN'T MIND HAVING
THAT DUDE ON MY TEAM.

27:32.738 --> 27:34.304
FOR REAL.
DUDE'S A BEAST.

27:34.348 --> 27:35.915
WHEN HE TACKLED ME
ON THAT SCREEN PASS,

27:35.958 --> 27:37.786
I THOUGHT I'D DIED
FOR A MINUTE.

27:37.830 --> 27:39.788
DON'T TELL HIM I SAID THAT.
SPENCER: HEH HEH! I WON'T.

27:39.832 --> 27:41.442
YO, IT'S BEEN DOPE
HAVING YOU

27:41.485 --> 27:43.444
ON THE SAME TEAM AGAIN, MAN.
CAM: OH, YEAH.

27:43.487 --> 27:45.446
I FEEL BAD FOR
THE DEFENSE, THOUGH.

27:45.489 --> 27:47.709
YOU WERE UNSTOPPABLE
OUT THERE, BRO.

27:47.753 --> 27:49.885
THANKS, AND IMAGINE
IF YOU NEVER LEFT
CRENSHAW.

27:49.929 --> 27:52.061
- MAN, YOU LEFT FIRST.
- BUT I CAME BACK.

27:52.105 --> 27:54.498
- YOU RIGHT.
- HEH HEH!

27:54.542 --> 27:57.719
YOU KNOW, OHIO'S GONNA
FEEL A LOT DIFFERENT
THAN CRENSHAW, BRO.

27:57.763 --> 27:59.939
YEAH, I KNOW.
SO WHERE YOU GOING?

27:59.982 --> 28:01.941
I'M ANNOUNCING
MY DECISION AT HALFTIME.

28:01.984 --> 28:03.594
YOU WANT TO GO
CHECK IT OUT?

28:03.638 --> 28:05.596
- MAYBE.
- ALL RIGHT, WHATEVER.

28:05.640 --> 28:07.598
- [CHUCKLING]
- HEY, YO, SPENCE?

28:07.642 --> 28:08.991
YO?

28:09.035 --> 28:10.993
TOLEDO STATE'S GOT THEM
SOME GREATNESS.

28:11.037 --> 28:13.387
THEY DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT'S COMING.

28:13.430 --> 28:15.389
YOU GONNA LIGHT
OHIO UP, BRO.

28:15.432 --> 28:17.783
THEY'RE LUCKY
TO HAVE YOU.

28:17.826 --> 28:21.308
YOU KNOW WHAT, CAM?
YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT.

28:29.446 --> 28:30.839
WE'LL SEE YOU
OUT THERE.

28:30.883 --> 28:32.972
BILLY: HEY.
HUDSON: GREAT FIRST HALF.

28:33.015 --> 28:34.974
THOSE YOUR PLAYERS
CARVING UP THAT 5-STAR
DEFENSE OUT THERE?

28:35.017 --> 28:36.889
HA HA! SOME OF THEM
WERE, BUT, UH,

28:36.932 --> 28:39.326
COACH MONTES HAD
SOME GEMS IN THERE, TOO.

28:39.369 --> 28:41.763
WOW. WELL, MAYBE
I SHOULD OFFER HER
THE JOB.

28:41.807 --> 28:44.374
[BOTH CHUCKLE]
BILLY: ACTUALLY,

28:44.418 --> 28:46.637
UM, MAYBE YOU SHOULD.

28:48.161 --> 28:50.337
OH. IS THIS WHERE
YOU TURN ME DOWN?

28:50.380 --> 28:53.340
OH, COACH, I WENT
BACK AND FORTH,
LIKE, 20 TIMES,

28:53.383 --> 28:55.559
BUT, UH, BUT, YEAH.

28:55.603 --> 28:58.171
I, UH, I'M GONNA HAVE
TO RESPECTFULLY DECLINE.

28:58.214 --> 29:00.782
I, UH, I APPRECIATE
YOU CONSIDERING ME,
THOUGH. I DO.

29:00.826 --> 29:03.219
I'M SORRY TO HEAR THAT.
CAN I ASK WHY?

29:03.263 --> 29:05.787
THIS IS A PRETTY BIG
OPPORTUNITY.

29:05.831 --> 29:07.789
IT IS A BIG OPPORTUNITY,
BUT I JUST FEEL

29:07.833 --> 29:09.791
LIKE SPENCER NEEDS
TO SPREAD HIS WINGS

29:09.835 --> 29:12.272
WITHOUT ME
BY HIS SIDE, YOU KNOW?

29:12.315 --> 29:15.841
AND TO BE HONEST, UH,
I HAVEN'T FIGURED OUT

29:15.884 --> 29:18.800
WHAT THIS NEXT
CHAPTER IS FOR ME.
HUDSON: OH.

29:18.844 --> 29:21.542
MAYBE I HAVEN'T
FINISHED EVERYTHING I
WAS SUPPOSED TO DO HERE,

29:21.585 --> 29:24.675
BUT AGAIN, I APPRECIATE
THE CONSIDERATION.

29:24.719 --> 29:27.766
- GOOD LUCK.
- THANKS COACH.

29:27.809 --> 29:31.160
REPORTER: IN TODAY'S
GAME, WE HAVE 12
ELITE PROSPECTS

29:31.204 --> 29:32.988
WHO ARE
CURRENTLY UNDECIDED.

29:33.032 --> 29:34.947
EIGHT OF THEM WILL
BE CHOOSING THEIR

29:34.990 --> 29:37.601
COLLEGE DESTINATION
LIVE, RIGHT NOW.

29:37.645 --> 29:39.995
FIRST UP IS 4-STAR
WIDE RECEIVER

29:40.039 --> 29:42.215
OUT OF WESTLAKE,
CALIFORNIA,
CAM WATKINS.

29:42.258 --> 29:45.566
CAM, I SEE YOU'VE
NARROWED IT DOWN
TO 4 LUCKY SCHOOLS.

29:45.609 --> 29:47.568
THE MOMENT IS
NOW YOURS.

29:47.611 --> 29:50.179
WHERE WILL YOU BE
SPENDING THE NEXT
4 YEARS?

29:50.223 --> 29:52.834
WELL, FIRST I'D LIKE
TO THANK GOD,

29:52.878 --> 29:56.446
UM, MY FAMILY,
MY COACHES, AND TEAMMATES.

29:56.490 --> 30:00.711
WITHOUT ANY OF THEM,
NONE OF THIS WOULD BE
POSSIBLE, SO THANK YOU.

30:00.755 --> 30:03.279
AND, WITH THAT
BEING SAID,

30:03.323 --> 30:06.369
I WILL BE TAKING
MY TALENTS TO...

30:08.328 --> 30:10.504
AND THE LUCKY
SCHOOL IS?

30:10.547 --> 30:12.811
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

30:15.204 --> 30:17.380
[SIGHS, SETS DOWN HAT]

30:25.432 --> 30:27.434
CAM: STAY TUNED.
[LAUGHTER]

30:27.477 --> 30:30.263
REPORTER:
OK, SO IT APPEARS
CAM WATKINS IS

30:30.306 --> 30:32.700
GOING TO REMAIN
UNDECIDED FOR

30:32.743 --> 30:35.311
A LITTLE WHILE LONGER.
STAY TUNED.

30:35.355 --> 30:37.052
[APPLAUSE]

30:37.096 --> 30:38.706
BAKER.

30:38.749 --> 30:40.099
YOU'RE IN.

30:40.142 --> 30:41.752
JORDAN: WHAT?
BILLY: GO GET 'EM.

30:41.796 --> 30:44.364
- YO!
- GET YOUR HELMET, BOY.

30:44.407 --> 30:46.366
- HELMET.
- RELAX, RELAX, RELAX.

30:46.409 --> 30:48.803
ISAIAH: ATTA BOY, J!
JORDAN: MY MAN.

30:48.847 --> 30:50.413
UM...

30:50.457 --> 30:53.460
COACH...CAN YOU
PUT ISAIAH IN?

30:55.157 --> 30:57.768
WINFIELD,
GRAB A HELMET.

30:57.812 --> 30:59.205
- UH-OH.
- HEY.

30:59.248 --> 31:00.859
PLAYER: UH-OH!
PLAYER 2: LET'S DO THIS.

31:00.902 --> 31:02.773
YO, YOU DID THAT
FOR ME?

31:02.817 --> 31:04.775
YOU EARNED THIS, ALL RIGHT?
IT'S OUR TIME NOW.

31:04.819 --> 31:07.082
WE BOTH TURNED IT INTO FUEL.
LET'S PLAY SOME FOOTBALL.

31:07.126 --> 31:08.910
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

31:08.954 --> 31:10.912
STADIUM ANNOUNCER:
WESTERN RESERVE JORDAN BAKER

31:10.956 --> 31:13.088
OUT OF CALIFORNIA CHECKS IN
TO QUARTERBACK.

31:13.132 --> 31:15.264
[PLAYERS SHOUTING]

31:15.308 --> 31:18.180
ANNOUNCER: TAKES THE SNAP,
THIRD AND LONG.

31:18.224 --> 31:20.835
QUICK PASS
TO ISAIAH WINFIELD,

31:20.879 --> 31:24.317
AND HE GETS THE FIRST DOWN!
[CROWD CHEERS]

31:24.360 --> 31:26.101
MALE SINGER:
♪ I KNOW WHAT...

31:26.145 --> 31:29.104
JORDAN: HERE YOU GO.
GUN RIGHT CHAIR ON 1.
READY?

31:29.148 --> 31:31.759
HEY, HEY, DON'T LET ME
OVERTHROW YOU.

31:31.802 --> 31:33.979
ISAIAH: NOT POSSIBLE.
JORDAN: ALL RIGHT.

31:34.022 --> 31:37.373
- ♪ LET'S MAKE
A TOAST TO THE REBELS ♪
- HERE WE GO. DOWN, SET.

31:37.417 --> 31:40.072
WIDE 60.
WIDE, SET, HUT!

31:41.812 --> 31:44.772
ANNOUNCER: BAKER ROLLS OUT,
THROWS A DEEP BALL
TO WINFIELD.

31:44.815 --> 31:47.949
- ♪ CAN'T WORRY
'BOUT YESTERDAY ♪
- TOUCHDOWN!

31:47.993 --> 31:50.386
- WHOO!
- NICE PASS, BRO.

31:50.430 --> 31:52.954
SPENCER: HA HA!
HERE COME J!

31:52.998 --> 31:56.001
[MUSIC AND SINGING STOP]

31:56.044 --> 31:57.916
IF YOU THINK
YOU'LL FINISH
WRITING BY SUMMER,

31:57.959 --> 31:59.526
I'LL JUST
GO AHEAD AND BOOK
THE MUSICIANS NOW

31:59.569 --> 32:01.528
SO THEY'LL BE
AVAILABLE TO RECORD.

32:01.571 --> 32:04.748
- OK, I'M GOOD WITH THAT.
- OK, SO I'LL DO IT IN--

32:04.792 --> 32:06.750
COOP: WHAT'S UP, LAYLA?
LAYLA: HEY.

32:06.794 --> 32:08.752
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
AT SPENCER'S GAME.
[COOP SIGHS]

32:08.796 --> 32:11.712
I WAS, AND ACTUALLY,
I CAN'T STAY. I JUST--

32:11.755 --> 32:14.106
I WANTED
TO APOLOGIZE FOR
THE PAST COUPLE DAYS.

32:14.149 --> 32:16.108
I MEAN, ONE MINUTE,
I'M ACCUSING YOU
OF BEING YOUR POPS,

32:16.151 --> 32:18.110
WHICH YOU'RE NOT,
AND THE NEXT,
I'M WALKING OUT

32:18.153 --> 32:20.112
OF THE STUDIO WITHOUT
EXPLAINING MYSELF.

32:20.155 --> 32:23.115
IT'S TOO HARD
TO ACTUALLY...BE
INVOLVED IN THE MIX,

32:23.158 --> 32:25.769
KNOWING MY DREAM IS
GONE, EVEN THOUGH
I MISS IT.

32:25.813 --> 32:28.729
AND HOPEFULLY,
I'LL GET THERE.
I DON'T KNOW,

32:28.772 --> 32:31.340
BUT I DO KNOW THAT YOU
HAVE TO FIND A WAY

32:31.384 --> 32:33.473
TO FINISH THESE TRACKS,
AND I GET IT.

32:33.516 --> 32:36.171
WELL, LIKE I TOLD YOU,
I WISH IT WAS YOU
IN THAT BOOTH.

32:36.215 --> 32:38.565
ME, TOO, BUT THAT
NEW ARTIST, UH...

32:38.608 --> 32:41.437
- KIM NITTY.
- YEAH. SHE'S DOPE.

32:41.481 --> 32:43.439
I KNEW IT THE FIRST TIME
I SEEN HER

32:43.483 --> 32:45.441
LAST YEAR,
WHEN I BATTLED HER.

32:45.485 --> 32:49.445
SHE CAN GET IT DONE,
BUT IF I'M BEING HONEST,

32:49.489 --> 32:52.666
UM, SHE DOESN'T
REALLY SOUND RIGHT

32:52.709 --> 32:55.277
SINGING MY LYRICS
BECAUSE IT'S
MY EXPERIENCES.

32:55.321 --> 32:57.279
IT'S NOT HER FAULT,

32:57.323 --> 32:59.934
BUT I'VE SEEN HER
DO HER THING,

32:59.978 --> 33:01.544
SO LET HER FREESTYLE.

33:01.588 --> 33:04.852
SAME SOUND,
HER EXPERIENCES.

33:04.895 --> 33:07.507
I THINK IT COULD ADD
SOMETHING MAGICAL
TO THE TRACK.

33:07.550 --> 33:09.204
YOU MIGHT BE RIGHT.

33:09.248 --> 33:11.859
COOP: I KNOW I'M RIGHT.
PATIENCE: OK.

33:11.902 --> 33:14.253
COOP: WHATEVER. I'LL SEE
Y'ALL AROUND, THOUGH.
LAYLA: OK.

33:14.296 --> 33:16.995
PATIENCE: I LOVE YOU.
COOP: LOVE YOU.

33:18.953 --> 33:21.303
WELL, THAT WENT WELL.
THAT'S A START.

33:21.347 --> 33:24.002
- HA! OK.
- RIGHT?

33:24.045 --> 33:25.916
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

33:25.960 --> 33:29.007
WOMAN: OH, MY GOSH.
DID YOU SEE THAT TOUCHDOWN?

33:29.050 --> 33:31.183
ASHER: NICE PASS.
JORDAN: I THOUGHT
THAT YOU WEREN'T COMING.

33:31.226 --> 33:33.185
IF I WOULD HAVE MISSED
THAT TOUCHDOWN, I NEVER
WOULD HAVE HEARD

33:33.228 --> 33:34.838
THE END OF IT.
JORDAN: MMM, YOU THINK
YOU'RE GONNA HEAR

33:34.882 --> 33:36.449
THE END OF IT ANYWAY?
[ASHER CHUCKLES]

33:36.492 --> 33:38.277
- I'MMA HOLLER AT Y'ALL.
- YEAH.

33:38.320 --> 33:39.930
- YOU HUNGRY?
- I COULD EAT.

33:39.974 --> 33:41.845
I COULD EAT.
[SIGHS]

33:41.889 --> 33:43.847
HUDSON: AFTER WATCHING
THIS GAME,

33:43.891 --> 33:45.849
I THINK IT'S SAFE
TO SAY TOLEDO STATE

33:45.893 --> 33:48.461
GOT THE BEST PLAYER
IN THE COUNTRY.

33:48.504 --> 33:50.506
[BOTH CHUCKLE]
SPENCER: THANK YOU, COACH.

33:50.550 --> 33:53.509
LISTEN, I APPRECIATE YOU,
EVERYTHING YOU'VE DONE,

33:53.553 --> 33:56.512
GOING OUT OF YOUR WAY
TO BE HERE FOR ME TODAY...

33:56.556 --> 34:00.908
BUT I DON'T
THINK TOLEDO STATE'S
THE RIGHT FIT FOR ME,

34:00.951 --> 34:04.216
SO I'VE DECIDED
TO REOPEN MY RECRUITMENT.

34:04.259 --> 34:07.871
- WHO--WHO PAID YOU?
- WHO PAID ME?

34:07.915 --> 34:10.657
I'M NOT STUPID. I KNOW
SOME OF THESE SCHOOLS
GOT DEEP POCKETS.

34:10.699 --> 34:13.225
- THAT AIN'T WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.
- RIGHT. SHOULD HAVE KNOWN

34:13.268 --> 34:15.270
SOMETHING WAS UP
WHEN BILLY TURNED ME DOWN.
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

34:15.313 --> 34:17.967
HUDSON: I OFFERED BILLY
COACH DANTE'S OLD JOB.

34:18.012 --> 34:20.580
BEST COACHING OPPORTUNITY
OF HIS CAREER,

34:20.623 --> 34:23.190
AND HE JUST TURNED ME DOWN
AT HALFTIME, AND NOW THIS.

34:23.235 --> 34:25.846
YEAH, I GUESS
YOU TWO GOT OFFERED

34:25.889 --> 34:28.239
A BETTER PACKAGE DEAL.

34:28.283 --> 34:30.764
[SCOFFS, MUTTERS]

34:50.088 --> 34:52.655
[BILLY SIGHS]
SPENCER: WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME

34:52.699 --> 34:55.353
TOLEDO STATE OFFERED YOU
COACH DANTE'S JOB?

34:55.397 --> 34:57.573
BECAUSE I DIDN'T
WANT TO INFLUENCE
YOUR DECISION.

34:57.617 --> 35:00.010
AND IT WOULD HAVE.

35:00.054 --> 35:02.883
COACH, WE COULD HAVE
RUN IT BACK FOR FOUR
MORE YEARS.

35:02.926 --> 35:06.582
BILLY: HEH HEH HEH!
BELIEVE ME, I
THOUGHT ABOUT IT,

35:08.323 --> 35:10.934
BUT IT'S, UH,

35:10.978 --> 35:13.807
TIME FOR SPENCER JAMES
TO FIND A NEW MENTOR.

35:13.850 --> 35:16.810
MAN, I LEARNED
SO MUCH FROM YOU, MAN.

35:16.853 --> 35:20.814
AND YOU'LL
CONTINUE TO LEARN,
FROM OTHER COACHES.

35:20.857 --> 35:22.859
YOUR CAREER IS
JUST BEGINNING.

35:31.390 --> 35:34.436
- IT JUST HIT ME.
- WHAT?

35:35.959 --> 35:37.961
THAT'S REALLY IT.

35:39.485 --> 35:42.531
- WE HAD A GOOD RUN, DIDN'T WE?
- YEAH.

35:45.534 --> 35:48.146
[SIGHS]

35:48.189 --> 35:51.845
THANK YOU FOR COMING
INTO MY LIFE...

35:53.803 --> 35:57.111
FOR EVERYTHING
YOU DID FOR ME.

35:59.331 --> 36:02.377
I'LL NEVER FORGET
THESE LAST TWO YEARS
TOGETHER.

36:05.946 --> 36:07.991
NEITHER WILL I.

36:11.256 --> 36:13.040
[SIGHS]

36:19.307 --> 36:21.570
KIM: YO, SAME THING
FROM THE TOP?

36:21.614 --> 36:23.790
ACTUALLY,
WE'RE GONNA TRY
SOMETHING DIFFERENT.

36:23.833 --> 36:27.228
SO SAME ARRANGEMENT,
BUT I WANT YOU
TO FREESTYLE

36:27.272 --> 36:29.230
YOUR OWN LYRICS.
CAN YOU DO THAT?

36:29.274 --> 36:32.277
OK, LOOK, I'M
ALL ABOUT THAT.
LET'S GET IT.

36:32.320 --> 36:34.496
BACKGROUND VOCAL:
♪ NO QUESTIONS ASKED

36:34.540 --> 36:36.585
KIM: ♪ LOOK, FEEL BAD
FOR MY COMPETITION ♪

36:36.629 --> 36:38.326
♪ Y'ALL SHOULDA NEVER
LET ME IN THIS ♪

36:38.370 --> 36:40.067
♪ BEEN HAVIN' MY DUCKS
LINED UP IN A ROW ♪

36:40.110 --> 36:41.721
♪ WHEN YOU EVEN KNEW
HOW TO GO FISHIN' ♪

36:41.764 --> 36:43.331
♪ YEAH, I GOT THAT HEAT
LIKE FRICTION ♪

36:43.375 --> 36:44.985
♪ AND RESPECT
LIKE HILLARY CLINTON ♪

36:45.028 --> 36:46.900
♪ AS FAR AS Gs GO, YEAH,
I KNOW WHO FAKE ♪

36:46.943 --> 36:48.075
♪ YOU DON'T BE PRETENDIN'

36:48.118 --> 36:49.250
♪ I'M EATIN' CHEESE

36:49.294 --> 36:50.469
♪ SIPPIN' VINO

36:50.512 --> 36:51.774
♪ BOUGIE WITH A EGO

36:51.818 --> 36:53.036
♪ MIGHT HAVE TO CHANGE MY NAME

36:53.080 --> 36:55.038
♪ TO KIM NITTY BAMBINO

36:55.082 --> 36:58.216
♪ I AIN'T NEVER HIDIN',
Y'ALL KNOW WHERE TO FIND ME ♪

36:58.259 --> 37:01.915
♪ THIS GOES OUT TO EVERYBODY
TRY THEIR LUCK, DON'T TRY ME ♪

37:03.395 --> 37:05.353
HEY, CONGRATULATIONS.

37:05.397 --> 37:07.007
BILLY: YES.
OLIVIA: HEH HEH!

37:07.050 --> 37:09.836
YOUR BOY BALLED OUT TODAY,
AND AGAINST SOME

37:09.879 --> 37:11.838
OF THE BEST ATHLETES
IN THE COUNTRY.

37:11.881 --> 37:14.275
I KNOW.
I CAUGHT THE SECOND HALF
ON TV, AND I SAW JORDAN

37:14.319 --> 37:18.279
GOT INTO THE GAME, TOO.
SPENCER: HEY, THAT BOY
THREW A DIME FOR 50 YARDS.

37:18.323 --> 37:20.281
BILLY: I THINK HE
OPENED UP SOME EYES TODAY.
SPENCER: RIGHT.

37:20.325 --> 37:23.371
BILLY: HE OPENED UP SOME EYES.
OLIVIA: YEAH. HEH HEH HEH!

37:23.415 --> 37:26.374
YOU HAND IN
YOUR ASSIGNMENT?

37:26.418 --> 37:29.029
YEAH.

37:29.072 --> 37:32.032
AND I'M GUESSING
YOU AIN'T HEARD
NOTHING BACK?

37:32.075 --> 37:34.948
[PATS LEG]
I MEAN, I
DON'T EXPECT TO.

37:34.991 --> 37:37.429
I MEAN, THEY GAVE ME
A VERY CLEAR AND
SPECIFIC ASSIGNMENT.

37:37.472 --> 37:39.300
AND SIMONE AND I
RUINED IT.

37:39.344 --> 37:41.084
SORTA.
[SIGHS]

37:41.128 --> 37:45.306
I'M KIDDING.
I GAVE THEM
A GREAT STORY, BUT...

37:45.350 --> 37:48.309
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE FUN AND POPPY
JUST ISN'T MY THING,

37:48.353 --> 37:50.442
AND I'M OK WITH THAT.

37:50.485 --> 37:53.358
GOOD. YOU STILL WANT
TO WATCH A MOVIE?

37:53.401 --> 37:56.012
SURE. LET'S MAKE
SOME POPCORN.

37:56.056 --> 37:58.363
CAN THE MOVIE
BE FUN AND POPPY?

37:58.406 --> 38:00.278
- TOO SOON.
- SORRY.

38:00.321 --> 38:02.758
MALE SINGER: ♪ CAN YOU
GIVE IT ONE DAY? ♪

38:02.802 --> 38:04.978
JORDAN: DID YOU SEE ME
OUT THERE TODAY?
ASHER: I SAW.

38:05.021 --> 38:07.197
- WHEN I DUCKED OUT
THAT DEFENSIVE END?
- I WAS THERE, JORDAN.

38:07.241 --> 38:09.983
- YOU KNOW THAT GUY'S GOING
TO FLORIDA STATE, RIGHT?
- GOOD SCHOOL.

38:10.026 --> 38:13.073
I MEAN, I WAS JUST
AS GOOD AS EVERYONE ELSE
ON THAT FIELD TODAY.

38:13.116 --> 38:16.206
DUDE, IT'S OBVIOUS THAT YOU'RE
JUST AS GOOD AS ANY PLAYER
OUT THERE ON THE FIELD.

38:16.250 --> 38:21.211
THANK YOU, BUT, I MEAN,
THEY'RE ALL GOING POWER-5
D1, AND I'M GOING JUCO.

38:21.255 --> 38:23.213
OK...

38:23.257 --> 38:25.607
AND SO DID AARON RODGERS.
HE TURNED OUT ALL RIGHT.

38:25.651 --> 38:27.609
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

38:27.653 --> 38:29.872
YOU KNOW, HE PLAYED
JUCO FOR ONE YEAR,
AND HE SHOWED EVERYBODY

38:29.916 --> 38:32.092
HOW UNSTOPPABLE
HE WAS.

38:32.135 --> 38:34.834
AFTER THAT, HE PRETTY MUCH
GOT TO PICK WHATEVER
SCHOOL HE WANTED.

38:34.877 --> 38:36.836
I CAN DO THAT.

38:36.879 --> 38:39.055
ONE YEAR, BALL OUT,

38:39.099 --> 38:42.058
SHOW EVERYONE WHAT
I'M CAPABLE OF.
I MEAN...

38:42.102 --> 38:46.062
HEH! TODAY, I CHANGED
THE WAY I VIEW MYSELF.

38:46.106 --> 38:48.064
NEXT YEAR, I'M
GONNA CHANGE THE WAY

38:48.108 --> 38:50.937
EVERYONE ELSE SEES ME.
I GUARANTEE YOU.

38:50.980 --> 38:53.461
[MOURNFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

38:53.505 --> 38:56.116
OLIVIA: I THOUGHT THIS
WAS SUPPOSED TO BE FUNNY.

38:56.159 --> 38:59.337
IT WAS IN
THE COMEDY SECTION,
BUT, UH, IT DEFINITELY

38:59.380 --> 39:02.340
TOOK A TURN, KIND OF
LIKE YOUR ASSIGNMENT.

39:02.383 --> 39:03.950
REALLY?

39:03.993 --> 39:05.560
OH, I THOUGHT WE
WERE STILL DOING

39:05.604 --> 39:07.214
THE BACK-AND-FORTH
JOKE THING.

39:07.257 --> 39:09.390
OH, NO, NO, NO, THAT--
THAT TIME HAS PASSED.

39:09.434 --> 39:12.132
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]
SPENCER: OH, PHONE.

39:14.439 --> 39:17.050
OH, MY GOD.
IT'S THE EDITOR.

39:17.093 --> 39:20.053
HEY.
[TURNS OFF TV]

39:20.096 --> 39:22.055
AHEM.

39:22.098 --> 39:24.057
HELLO?

39:24.100 --> 39:25.667
HI.

39:25.711 --> 39:28.757
YEAH--NO, NO,
IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

39:31.369 --> 39:34.328
[SIGHS]
YES, I--I KNOW IT...
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

39:34.372 --> 39:37.331
WASN'T WHAT YOU ASKED FOR.
UM, IT JUST...

39:37.375 --> 39:40.378
KINDA TOOK ON A LIFE
OF ITS OWN.
[PATS LEG]

39:42.380 --> 39:46.993
YEAH, I UNDERSTAND.
YOU FOUND SOMEONE?
THAT'S...GREAT.

39:47.036 --> 39:50.213
UM...LISTEN, UM,

39:50.257 --> 39:53.434
I'M--I'M SORRY THAT I
COULDN'T DELIVER WHAT--
WHAT YOU WANTED.

39:53.478 --> 39:55.784
I JUST...

39:55.828 --> 39:57.482
OH.

39:59.484 --> 40:01.442
UH, OK.

40:01.486 --> 40:03.270
THANK YOU.

40:03.313 --> 40:05.968
[CHUCKLES]
OK. OK, BYE.

40:13.149 --> 40:16.109
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT
ABOUT TO LEAVE ME
HANGING RIGHT NOW.

40:16.152 --> 40:18.720
- I GOT IT. HA HA!
- YOU GOT IT?

40:18.764 --> 40:20.853
[LAUGHING]

40:20.896 --> 40:23.856
SHE SAID THAT THEY FOUND
A FUN AND POPPY WRITER,

40:23.899 --> 40:26.467
BUT THEY LOVED
WHAT I SENT THEM,

40:26.511 --> 40:29.862
AND THERE'S ALWAYS A PLACE
FOR GREAT STORIES LIKE THAT
IN THEIR PUBLICATION.

40:29.905 --> 40:32.299
SPENCER: YEAH, THERE IS.
MALE SINGER: ♪ DOING MY BEST

40:32.342 --> 40:35.258
- [GIGGLES]
- ♪ NOW I'M HOLDING ON,
I'M UP IN THE AIR ♪

40:35.302 --> 40:39.262
♪ NOBODY CARES,
ALL OF THESE CHANGES... ♪
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

40:39.306 --> 40:41.264
BILLY: HMM.

40:41.308 --> 40:43.702
THIS IS BILLY BAKER.

40:43.745 --> 40:45.878
HUDSON: BILLY,
LARRY HUDSON.

40:45.921 --> 40:48.315
UH, COACH HUDSON, UM,

40:48.358 --> 40:50.926
HEY, SO I HEARD ABOUT,

40:50.970 --> 40:53.929
UH, SPENCER
DECOMMITTING, AND, UM--

40:53.973 --> 40:56.366
ACTUALLY, THAT'S WHY
I'M CALLING YOU.

40:56.410 --> 40:59.500
SPENCER CAN EITHER
HEAR THIS FROM ME OR
FROM YOU. YOU DECIDE.

40:59.544 --> 41:01.676
- HEAR WHAT?
- WE PASSED ON
A LOT OF TOP PLAYERS

41:01.720 --> 41:03.896
AT SPENCER'S POSITION
WHEN HE SIGNED WITH US.

41:03.939 --> 41:06.725
THEY ARE OBVIOUSLY NOT
AVAILABLE ANYMORE.

41:06.768 --> 41:10.511
THIS LEAVES US
IN A VERY
DIFFICULT SITUATION.

41:10.555 --> 41:12.774
OK, WHAT ARE--
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

41:12.818 --> 41:16.256
WE'RE NOT GONNA
LET SPENCER OUT OF HIS
BINDING LETTER OF INTENT.

41:16.299 --> 41:18.650
- WELL, YOU CAN'T DO THAT.
- IT'S DONE.

41:18.693 --> 41:21.653
WE EXPECT SPENCER
TO HONOR THE COMMITMENT
TO US, WHICH MEANS HE

41:21.696 --> 41:24.873
CAN COME TO TOLEDO STATE,
HAVE A GREAT CAREER,

41:24.917 --> 41:28.094
OR HE GOES SOMEWHERE ELSE,
HE'LL BE INELIGIBLE

41:28.137 --> 41:30.313
TO PLAY FOOTBALL
HIS ENTIRE FRESHMAN YEAR.

41:30.357 --> 41:32.402
[HANGS UP PHONE]

41:34.492 --> 41:37.930
SINGER: ♪ GOT TO WASH IT ALL
AWAY NOW AND LET IT GO ♪

41:37.973 --> 41:39.540
[VOCALIZING]

41:39.584 --> 41:41.542
[OLIVIA LAUGHING]

41:41.586 --> 41:45.241
SINGER: ♪ I CAN'T LIVE
LIKE THIS NO MORE ♪

42:15.968 --> 42:17.491
MAN: GREG, MOVE YOUR HEAD!
